===Etymology===
From Middle English ''[[slep]]'', Old English ''[[slæpan|slæp]]''.

=== Pronunciation ===
*slēp, /sliːp/, /<tt>sli:p</tt>/
*:[[Rhymes:English:-iːp|Rhymes: -iːp]]

===Noun===
{{en-noun|sleep|sleeps}}

#''(uncountable)'' An [[unconscious]] [[state]] during which a [[human]] or [[animal]] rests.
#:''I really need some '''sleep'''''.
#''(countable)'' (''colloquial'') An act or instance of sleeping.
#:''I'm just going to have a quick '''sleep'''''.
#''(uncountable)'' Substance found in the corner of the eyes after waking.<!-- slang or colloquial? usage outside Australia? -->
#:''Wipe the '''sleep''' from your eyes''.

